# Profiles + scoped research (v2 §2.6 / §2.7)

## Two profiles

| Profile                  | When picked (default) | Demo produced?  |
|--------------------------|-----------------------|-----------------|
| `full_pipeline`          | No `scoped_input`     | Yes             |
| `research_and_docs_only` | `scoped_input` present AND `generate_prototype_demo: false` | **No** |

The choice happens in the `SELECT_PROFILE` stage immediately after
`CLARIFY`. The orchestrator records the decision in the audit log.

## Scoped types and their layer-doc focus

| `scoped_input.type` | Layer docs generated by default                                 |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `topic`             | `foundation_theory + atomic_algorithm + tech_topic`              |
| `algorithm`         | `foundation_theory + atomic_algorithm`                           |
| `theory`            | `foundation_theory`                                              |
| `product`           | all four layers                                                  |

When ambiguous, the `scope-router` sub-agent narrows the search queries
by prepending the scoped name and scales each query's `max_results`
down by `scoped_input.quota_scale_factor` (default 0.5).

## "No Demo by default" (§5 / §8)

Under `research_and_docs_only`:

- `BUILD_DEMO`, `GENERATE_TESTS_AND_CI`, and `EXECUTE_TESTS` are SKIPPED.
- The orchestrator still runs `ALIGNMENT_REPORT` (against SRS/TDD) so
  the audit trail has a coverage verdict.
- The user can opt into a Demo at clarification or sign-off time by
  setting `task_input.generate_prototype_demo: true`. Record that
  decision in the audit log.

## Knowledge base (§2.8)

If `task_input.knowledge_base` is set, the `kb-connector` sub-agent
populates `ctx.kb_snapshot` before research. Downstream layer-doc
writers MUST prefer existing KB docs over re-deriving content and MUST
mark conflicts in `LayerDoc.conflicts`.
